      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (NIH, RH index, wall shear stress) must be directly linked to the clinical hemolysis decision at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH, derived from NIH predictions. RH directly determines whether the pump design meets the predicate comparison criterion. Clinical relevance established through literature and FDA guidance."
